Articles.Content:
Did another test flight with the MU Ingressor-class ship A.D.A. today:

Needless to say, it went well. Bob even got to check out some space hulks around Eeloo.

@daemon, you ready to battle some more?

EDIT: Since MinusUdn appears to have left, can we mark that down as a victory by default?

I know I went inactive while we were battling, but family matters occurred and were unavoidable.

EDIT 2x: Also, anyone get the reference in my ship's name?

Edited May 11, 2014 by ScriptKitt3h

Revival update

My updated fleet is near compleat

Salvation mkV is near finished but I'm going to try to make it a lil better (just for kicks)

Gospel Class convention to frigate was successful but am going to continue to make improvements

New idea came to me for faithful design. Will try out later.

Should be ready to battle again soon

@Tarzan I made my move, but I forgot to turn on my mic, so the video only has the game footage.

Video will be up soon

Persistent:g57c/persistent.sfs"]https://www.dropbox.com/s/ber5cje885yg57c/persistent.sfs

Edited May 11, 2014 by AvronMullican
Sorry, but submitting persist might take me some time as lag goes to space and I have A LOT of crashes. @ScriptKitt3h, how many parts have "Hawking"? It's killing my PC

Sorry, but submitting persist might take me some time as lag goes to space and I have A LOT of crashes. @ScriptKitt3h, how many parts have "Hawking"? It's killing my PC

As I've stated before, the hawking-class is around 500 parts WITH ammo. To lower the partcount, re-arm it by getting rid of the ammo I used.

Weird. It should not be that bad if so o.O

EDIT: Seems that "Tiger" needs some work on it. You had a lucky shot though, test rendered that its armour is actually pretty tough against all kind of projectiles

Edited May 11, 2014 by Tarzan

persist I managed to damage (but not destroy) the "Hawking". Finally. After something about 15 crashes -.- I think that something is not ok with my PC. It was always slow, but never that much. Right now I even have problems with my browser o.O

Screenshots - I don't have energy for descriptions after that fight against my computer

Edited May 11, 2014 by Tarzan
Is okay if I delete some of the debris Field
sure, just don't delete main part of "Kerchak" as there is a lot of ammo to reload

Damaged the Shere Khan,

Should be ready to battle again soon

I fight? I changed the engines on the cargo SSTO to nukes which brought the D/V up by 200, the mass down by 90, and the carrying capacity up by 25%. I just wish it looked good:(
